properties.areaDesc: Santa Ana Mountains and Foothills; Riverside County Mountains; San Bernardino County Mountains; San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning; San Bernardino and Riverside County Valleys-The Inland Empire
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 28 at 1:07PM PST until January 30 at 1:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
expected. Isolated gusts to 70 mph.

* WHERE...San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning, Santa Ana Mountains
and Foothills, Riverside County Mountains, San Bernardino
County Mountains and San Bernardino and Riverside County
Valleys-The Inland Empire.

* WHEN...From 6 AM Wednesday to 1 PM PST Thursday. Strongest winds
expected Wednesday evening into Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds could blow down trees and power lines.
Power outages are possible. Travel will be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Difficult travel for high profile vehicles
especially along Interstate 15 through and below Cajon Pass,
Interstate 215 below Cajon Pass, and Interstate 10 through the
San Gorgonio Pass.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM WEDNESDAY TO 1 PM PST THURSDAY
